ficial%20of%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20mean%20paralyzing%20one%20of%20the%20most%20promising%20technologies%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vance%20of%20overregulation%2C%20citing%20benefits%20in%20fields%20such%20as%20economic%20innovation%2C%20job%20creation%2C%20national%20security%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20free%20expression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVance%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20excessive%20regulation%20of%20the%20AI%20sector%20could%20kill%20a%20transformative%20industry%20just%20as%20it's%20taking%20off%2C%20and%20we'll%20make%20every%20effort%20to%20encourage%20pro-growth%20AI%20policies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20would%20focus%20on%20building%20AI%20systems%20in%20the%20US%20chips%20designed%20and%20made%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20spread%20those%20advances%20internationally%2C%20he%20said%2C%20other%20countries%20needed%20to%20cut%20their%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20create%20that%20kind%20of%20trust%2C%20we%20need%20international%20regulatory%20regimes%20that%20foster%20the%20creation%20of%20AI%20technology%20rather%20than%20strangle%20it%2C%20and%20we%20need%20our%20European%20friends%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20to%20look%20to%20this%20new%20frontier%20with%20optimism%20rather%20than%20trepidation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20on%20to%20warn%20against%20new%20regulations%20against%20US%20tech%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Trump%20administration%20is%20troubled%20by%20reports%20that%20some%20foreign%20governments%20are%20considering%20tightening%20the%20screws%20on%20US%20tech%20companies%20with%20international%20footprints%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20America%20cannot%20and%20will%20not%20accept%20that%2C%20and%20we%20think%20it's%20a%20terrible%20mistake%2C%20not%20just%20for%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%2C%20but%20for%20your%20own%20countries.%