orce%20recently%20surpassed%20that%20of%20baby%20boomers%2C%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20expected%20to%20account%20for%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20global%20workforce%20this%20year.%20Their%20transformation%20into%20a%20chatbot%20generation%20could%20have%20a%20seismic%20effect%20on%20the%20workplace.%20As%20employers%20look%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20tech's%20productivity%20gains%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-job-build-ai-skills-help-change-roles-employers-hiring-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20proficiency%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20becoming%20a%20prerequisite%20for%20many%20jobs%2C%20leaving%20behind%20those%20who%20aren't%20as%20fast%20in%20adopting%20it.%20Amid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fas-employee-confidence-in-ais-potential-grows-so-does-anxiety-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanxiety%20about%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20taking%20away%20job%20opportunities%2C%20many%20young%20people%20are%20skilling%20up%20to%20try%20to%20stay%20hirable.%20But%20some%20experts%20are%20worried%20that%20operating%20on%20AI%20autopilot%20could%20come%20back%20to%20bite%20Gen%20Z%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMonique%20Buksh%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20law%20student%20and%20paralegal%20in%20Australia%2C%20has%20found%20AI%20to%20be%20an%20immense%20time-saver.%20She%20uses%20Westlaw%20Edge%20and%20Lexis%2B%20to%20help%20with%20doing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fartificial-intelligence-use-in-law-firms-legal-cases-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20unearthing%20relevant%20case%20law%20and%20statutes.%20She%20also%20turns%20to%20Grammarly%20to%20draft%20official%20documents%20and%20the%20AI%20assistant%20Claude%20to%20spot%20inconsistencies%20in%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20AI%20handling%20time-consuming%20work%2C%20I'm%20able%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20discussions%20around%20str