%20fall%20found%20that%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-surging-ai-automating-jobs-unemployment-labor-market-white-collar-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%2C000%20jobs%20were%20cut%20in%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20AI.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fmgi%2Foverview%2Fin-the-news%2Fwill-generative-ai-be-good-for-us-workers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusiness.edx.org%2Fwhite-paper%2Fnavigating-the-workplace-in-the-age-of-ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eothers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20forecast%20that%20entry-level%20roles%2C%20which%20Gen%20Z%20predominates%2C%20will%20be%20the%20first%20cut%20back%20by%20automation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Microsoft%20and%20LinkedIn%20survey%20of%2031%2C000%20knowledge%20workers%20conducted%20last%20year%2C%20for%20example%2C%20suggested%20that%20AI%20could%20fast-track%20Gen%20Zers'%20professional%20trajectory.%20Among%20the%20workers%20in%20leadership%20surveyed%2C%2071%25%20said%20they'd%20prefer%20hiring%20candidates%20with%20AI%20expertise%20over%20those%20with%20more%20conventional%20experience%2C%20and%20nearly%2080%25%20said%20they'd%20give%20AI-savvy%20staffers%20greater%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETatiana%20Becker%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20tech%20recruiting%2C%20says%20that%20ultimately%2C%20%26quot%3Bemployers%20will%20be%20more%20interested%20in%20people%20with%20AI%20skills%2C%20but%20at%20all%20levels%2C%20not%20just%20Gen%20Z%20workers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20people%20worry%20that%20using%20AI%20as%20a%20shortcut%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-ai-bad-bosses-replace-young-employees-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehurt%20Gen%20Z%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20In%20an%20online%20survey%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20used%20AI%20at%20work%20by%20TalentLMS%2C%20which%20provides%20e-learning%20software%20for%20companies%2C%2040%25%20of%20respondents%20indicated%20they%20believed%20AI%20hindered%20their%20growth%20by%20doing%20tasks%20they%20could%20have%20learned%20from.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2075-4698%2F15%2F1%2F6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnother%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20that%20heavy%20reliance%20on%20AI%20tools%20was%20associated%20with%20lower%20measures%20of%20critical%20thinking%2C%20especially%20among%20younger%20adults.%20A%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.404media.co%2Fmicrosoft-study-finds-ai-makes-human-cognition-atrophied-and-unprepared-3%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20researchers%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University%20found%20something%20similar%3A%20the%20more%20people%20used%20and%20trusted%20AI%2C%20the%20less%20they%20relied%20on%20critical%20thinking%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20concerning%3A%20About%20half%20of%20Gen%20Z%20respondents%20in%20a%20survey%20by%20Workplace%20Intelligence%2C%20an%20industry%20research%20agency%2C%20and%20INTOO%2C%20a%20talent%20development%20firm%2C%20said%20they%20turned%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-ai-chatgpt-for-career-advice-motivation-workplace-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20AI%20for%20guidance%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20their%20managers.%20Erica%20Keswin%2C%20an%20author%20and%20workplace%20strategist%2C%20isn't%20surprised.%20Many%20Gen%20Zers%20missed%20out%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-training-broken-gen-z-mentorship-companies-employees-managers-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritical%20in-person%20mentorship%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20college%20and%20in%20early-career%20roles%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BMany%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20aren't%20comfortable%20connecting%20with%20their%20managers%20IRL%20to%20have%20difficult%20conversations%20and%20may%20find%20it%20easier%20to%20pose%20questions%20to%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20AI%2C%20unlike%20managers%2C%20is%20constantly%20accessible%20and%20immediate%20and%20provides%20answers%20without%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20can%20have%20downsides.%20Golden%2C%20of%20Deloitte%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-innovation-collaboration-return-to-office-work-from-home-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollaboration%20and%20innovation%3C%2Fa%3E%20thrive%20on%20the%20messiness%20of%20human%20interaction.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20real%20risk%20of%20weakening%20Gen%20Z's%20ability%20to%20navigate%20ambiguity%20and%20build%20the%20interpersonal%20skills%20that%20are%20essential%20in%20any%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20reason%20Nicholas%20Portello%2C%20a%20Gen%20Z%20professional%20in%20New%20York%2C%20is%20resisting%20using%20AI%20software.%20He%20thinks%20the%20instant%20gratification%20AI%20provides%20can%20harm%20productivity%20and%20creativity.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20best%20ideas%20my%20team%20and%20I%20produced%20in%202024%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20brainstorming%20sessions%20and%20environments%20of%20open%20communication%20as%20opposed%20to%20ChatGPT%2C%26quot%3B%20Portello%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyle%20Jensen%2C%20an%20English%20professor%20and%20director%20of%20writing%20programs%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University%2C%20thinks%20it's%20an%20avoidable%20problem.%20He%20says%20that%20for%20AI%20to%20supplement%20rather%20than%20replace%20a%20young%20person's%20analytical%20capabilities%2C%20they%20must%20develop%20expertise%20in%20a%20field%20or%20topic.%20He%20tries%20to%20encourage%20his%20students%20to%20reflect%20on%20AI%20tools'%20role%20in%20problem-solving%3A%20What%20kinds%20of%20problems%20would%20they%20be%20most%20useful%20for%3F%20When%20would%20they%20be%20less%20useful%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJensen%20argues%20that%20once%20a%20person%20acquires%20an%20in-depth%20understanding%20of%20a%20subject%20area%2C%20they%20can%20learn%20to%20recognize%20when%20a%20generative%20AI%20output%20is%20%26quot%3Boverly%20general%2C%20unhelpful%20to%20the%20problem%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20solve%2C%20incorrect%2C%20or%20exclusionary%20of%20different%20ways%20of%20knowing%20or%20feeling.%26quot%3B%20This%20also%20helps%20them%20pose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-get-better-chatgpt-ai-prompt-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20creative%20prompts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20could%20be%20a%20great%20leveling%20force%20within%20the%20workplace%2C%20giving%20younger%20workers%20a%20massive%20leg%20up.%20But%20the%20experts%20I%20talked%20to%20expect%20that%20as%20Gen%20Z%20gets%20a%20head%20start%20in%20AI%2C%20the%20workplace%20will%20be%20divided%20between%20those%20who%20use%20AI%20and%20those%20who%20don't.%20Over%20time%2C%20this%20could%20push%20out%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20already%20perpetuate%20the%20problem%20by%20tailoring%20training%20opportunities%20to%20only%20the%20youngest%20staffers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.randstadusa.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbusiness-insights%2Ffuture-work%2Fgenerational-divide-ai-adoption%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVarious%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greatplacetowork.com%2Fresources%2Fblog%2Fthe-best-workplaces-for-millennials-will-thrive-in-ai-world-thanks-to-employee-trust%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-employee-engagement-workplace-morale-careers-boomers-gen-x-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20tended%20to%20be%20given%20more%20opportunities%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20than%20older%20workers.%20Stephanie%20Forrest%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20TFD%2C%20a%20London-based%20marketing%20agency%2C%20warns%20other%20employers%20against%20counting%20out%20older%20workers.%20%26quot%3BIt%20shouldn't%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20foregone%20conclusion%20that%20these%20generations%20will%20be%20less%20capable%20%E2%80%94%20or%20less%20willing%20%E2%80%94%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20provided%20the%20right%20support%20is%20given%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20employees%20and%20organizations%20that%20get%20ahead%20will%20be%20the%20ones%20that%20can%20effectively%20harness%20their%20people%20power%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20manager's%20ability%20to%20coach%2C%20mentor%2C%20and%20motivate%20or%20an%20employee's%20ability%20to%20persuade%20a%20client%20to%20stay%20with%20their%20company%20%E2%80%94%20because%20that's%20something%20AI%20can't%20do.%20Everyone%2C%20from%20Gen%20Z%20entrants%20to%20company%20execs%2C%20needs%20to%20know%20when%20AI%20is%20useful%20and%20when%20something%20needs%20a%20human%20touch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubham-agarwal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EShubham%20Agarwal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20technology%20journalist%20from%20Ahmedabad%2C%20India%2C%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Wired%2C%20The%20Verge%2C%20Fast%20Company%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-using-ai-chatbots-chatgpt-claude-work-career-jobs-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739268361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a6562abfebcc4d029e3bc7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-using-ai-chatbots-chatgpt-claude-work-career-jobs-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20can't%20beat%20'em%2C%20join%20'em%3A%20How