E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-robots-could-save-10-billion-a-year-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20fleet%20of%20warehouse%20robots%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20swelled%20to%20more%20than%20750%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20grow%20both%20in%20size%20and%20complexity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobots%20now%20perform%20a%20variety%20of%20tasks%20in%20Amazon's%20fulfillment%20centers%2C%20transporting%20packages%20around%20busy%20workspaces%2C%20sorting%20and%20consolidating%20items%20into%20storage%20systems%2C%20and%20making%20fit-to-size%20packaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20robotics%20efforts%20started%20when%20it%20acquired%20Kiva%20Systems%20for%20%24775%20million%20in%202012.%20Kiva's%20automated%20guided%20vehicles%20navigated%20by%20following%20barcode%20stickers%20placed%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20a%20warehouse.%20More%20than%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20Amazon%20now%20has%20more%20than%2016%2C000%20people%20working%20on%20robotics%20as%20its%20technology%20has%20become%20more%20sophisticated%2C%20including%20Proteus%2C%20a%20mobile%20robot%20that%20can%20move%20autonomously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvesting%20in%20robotics%20helps%20Amazon%20accomplish%20its%20goal%20of%20getting%20packages%20to%20customers%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%20Tye%20Brady%2C%20chief%20technologist%20at%20Amazon%20Robotics%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider.%20Robots%20also%20create%20efficiencies%20that%20will%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-robots-could-save-10-billion-a-year-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20save%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20some%20%2410%20billion%20a%20year%20by%202030%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20estimated%20in%20a%20recent%20research%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20have%20faster%20delivery%20times%20because%20of%20the%20work%20that%20we've%20done%20in%20robotics%2C%26quot%3B%20Brady%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20also%20pass%20on%20a%20lower%20cost.%20And%20we're%20creating%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20jobs%20because%20of%20the%20work%20that%20we've%20done%20in%20robotics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Amazon%20hired%20three%20of%20the%20robotics%20startup%20Covariant's%20founders%20and%20licensed%20some%20of%20its%20foundation%20models%20to%20bring%20flexibility%20and%20fluidity%20to%20its%20robotics.%20The%20company%20also%20launched%20the%20Amazon%20Industrial%20Innovation%20Fund%20in%202022%2C%20investing%20in%20companies%20innovating%20in%20emerging%20tech%20like%20robots.%20That%20includes%20an%20investment%20in%20Agility%20Robotics%2C%20which%20makes%20a%20bipedal%20robot%20called%20Digit%20that%20Amazon%20is%20testing%20in%20fulfillment%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20commitment%20for%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20for%20our%20startups%2C%20in%20order%20to%20help%20the%20startups%20and%20the%20community%20raise%20the%20capital%20that%20they%20need%20in%20order%20to%20do%20some%20of%20these%20great%20ideas%20that%20we%20think%20are%20going%20to%20help%20our%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20Brady%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20examples%20of%20the%20most%20advanced%20robots%20working%20in%20Amazon's%20fulfillment%20centers%2C%20and%20a%20bit%20about%20what%20they%20do%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EProteus%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226229%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon's%20fully%20autonomous%20robot%2C%20Proteus%2C%20travels%20around%20a%20warehouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d39f07bb3f854015b6502%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon's%20fully%20autonomous%20Proteus%20robot.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Amazon's%20earlier%20mobile%20robots%2C%20Proteus%20is%20fully%20autonomous.%20It%20uses%20sensors%20to%20navigate%20around%20objects%20in%20its%20path.%20It%20works%20more%20closely%20alongside%20Amazon%20employees%20and%20is%20not%20restricted%20to%20fenced-in%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProteus%20travels%20under%20package%20carts%20and%20then%20transports%20them%20to%20the%20fulfillment%20center's%20loading%20dock.%20Brady%20compared%20its%20skills%20to%20how%20humans%20make%20their%20way%20around%20a%20crowded%20cocktail%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTypically%20a%20robot%2C%20when%20it%20sees%20maybe%20three%2C%20four%2C%20or%20five%20people%20gathered%20together%2C%20maybe%20they're%20all%20talking%20in%20a%20circle%20or%20something%20like%20that%2C%20it'll%20just%20stop%20and%20wait%20for%20the%20folks%20to%20kind%20of%20disband%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20trying%20to%20navigate%20from%20one%20side%20of%20the%20room%20to%20the%20other%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Proteus%20system%20actually%20is%20capable%20of%20that.%20It%20doesn't%20just%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20launched%20in%20a%20Nashville%20fulfillment%20center%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESparrow%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon's%20robotic%20arm%20Sparrow%20lifts%20up%20items%20in%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d3654196626c40986068c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221769%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon's%20robotic%20arm%20Sparrow.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESparrow%20is%20Amazon's%20first%20robotic%20arm%20to%20handle%20individual%20items%20rather%20than%20packages.%20It%20uses%20computer%20vision%20and%20AI%20to%20pick%20items%20from%20containers%20and%20place%20them%20into%20totes.%20It's%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20an%20elephant%20trunk%20and%20capable%20of%20picking%20up%20more%20than%20200%20million%20different%20items%2C%20Brady%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20first%20introduced%20in%20a%20fulfillment%20center%20in%20Richmond%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESequoia%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20worker%20in%20fulfillment%20center%20takes%20items%20out%20of%20crates%20using%20its%20Sequoia%20robotics%20system%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d3a0f7bb3f854015b650e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESequoia%20combines%20AI%20and%20computer%20vision%20with%20robotics.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESequoia%20combines%20AI%2C%20robotics%2C%20and%20computer%20vision%20into%20one%20storage%20solution.%20Totes%20containing%20items%20are%20stored%20in%20a%20vertical%20platform%20system%20called%20a%20gantry.%20Robots%20then%20move%20those%20totes%20to%20ergonomic%20workstations%20where%20employees%20pick%20products%20to%20be%20shipped%20to%20customers.%20Once%20an%20employee%20picks%20items%20from%20the%20totes%2C%20Amazon's%20robotic%20arm%2C%20Sparrow%2C%20retrieves%20any%20remaining%20items%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20then%20consolidates%20them%20so%20that%20full%20totes%20can%20be%20returned%20to%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20says%20Sequoia%20allows%20the%20company%20to%20identify%20and%20store%20products%20as%20much%20as%2075%25%20more%20quickly%20than%20before.%20It%20was%20first%20introduced%20in%20a%20Houston%20fulfillment%20center%20in%202023%20and%20is%20at%20the%20center%20of%20Amazon's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Foperations%2Famazon-fulfillment-center-robotics-ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bnext-generation%26quot%3B%20fulfillment%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Shreveport%2C%20Louisiana%2C%20where%20it%20can%20handle%20more%20than%2030%20million%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHercules%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Blue%20Hercules%20robots%20move%20items%20around%20Amazon%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aa19f87bb3f854015c5846%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHercules%20is%20one%20of%20Amazon's%20earlier%20mobile%20robots.%20It%20is%20capable%20of%20lifting%20pods%20of%20up%20to%201%2C250%20pounds.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIntroduced%20in%20Sumner%2C%20Washington%2C%20in%202017%2C%20Hercules%20is%20one%20of%20Amazon's%20earlier%20mobile%20robots.%20It%20moves%20pods%20of%20items%20around%20a%20fenced%20area%20of%20the%20fulfillment%20center%20by%20using%20its%203D%20camera%20to%20reference%20markers%20on%20the%20floor.%20That%20camera%20also%20helps%20it%20differentiate%20between%20the%20various%20things%20that%20may%20be%20in%20its%20way%2C%20like%20people%2C%20pods%2C%20or%20other%20robots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20lift%20pods%20that%20weigh%20up%20to%201%2C250%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETitan%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Blue%20Titan%20robot%20in%20Amazon%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aa1a3d6630eb10385c166b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon's%20Titan%20robot%20can%20lift%20over%20one%20ton%20of%20weight.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETitan%20operates%20similarly%20to%20Hercules%20but%20can%20lift%20double%20the%20weight%2C%20up%20to%202%2C500%20pounds.%20It%20made%20its%20debut%20in%20San%20Antonio%20in%202017%20and%20is%20typically%20used%20for%20bigger%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPegasus%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blue%20Pegasus%20robot%20made%20by%20Amazon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67aa193d6630eb10385c162c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPegasus%20works%20in%20conjunction%20with%20a%20robotic%20arm.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20introduced%20in%202018%2C%20Pegasus%20is%20a%20cousin%20to%20the%20Hercules%20robot%20that%20incorporates%20a%20conveyor%20belt%20on%20top%20of%20the%20drive%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20finished%20packages%20from%20employees%20to%20a%20sorting%20area%20that's%20determined%20by%20the%20recipient's%20ZIP%20code.%20Using%20a%20route%20provided%20by%20Amazon's%20centralized%20planning%20system%2C%20it%20navigates%20until%20it%20finds%20the%20correct%20location%2C%20then%20drops%20packages%20through%20a%20chute%20in%20the%20floor%20to%20a%20loading%20dock%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPegasus%20works%20in%20conjunction%20with%20Amazon's%20robotic%20arm%20Robin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERobin%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221535%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon's%20robotic%20arm%20Robin%20operating%20in%20a%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d35c1eb4be2fff9a325fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobin%20was%20designed%20to%20pick%20up%20packages%20from%20conveyor%20belts.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERobin%20was%20Amazon's%20first%20robotic%20arm%2C%20introduced%20in%20Lakeland%2C%20Florida%2C%20in%202022.%20It%20works%20in%20tandem%20with%20other%20robotic%20systems%2C%20picking%20up%20packages%20from%20conveyor%20belts%20and%20placing%20them%20on%20Pegasus%20mobile%20robots%20that%20bring%20them%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20fulfillment%20center.%20It%20also%20handles%20damaged%20packages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECardinal%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221267%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon's%20Cardinal%20robotic%20arm%20picks%20up%20packages%20in%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d3620eb4be2fff9a32613%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22950%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECardinal%20is%20a%20robotic%20arm%20designed%20for%20sorting%20packages.%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%