C%20a%20wealth%20strategist%20at%20TD%20Wealth.%20In%20fact%2C%20it's%20far%20from%20a%20foregone%20conclusion.%20And%20if%20the%20plan%20is%20not%20renewed%2C%20taxes%20are%20set%20to%20rise%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20some%20pretty%20serious%20philosophical%20divides%20in%20the%20Republican%20conference%20regarding%20the%20need%20to%20reduce%20our%20deficit%20versus%20the%20utility%20of%20extended%20tax%20cuts%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20guarantee%20that%20it's%20going%20to%20extend%20every%20single%20provision%20of%20the%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act%2C%20so%20the%20best%20you%20can%20do%20is%20assume%20nothing%20and%20plan%20within%20the%20rules%20as%20they%20exist%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20taxpayers%20should%20be%20aware%20of%20these%20two%20tax-saving%20movies%20that%20could%20come%20in%20handy%20if%20taxes%20are%20higher%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe59f5b1-92e5-4873-a925-fae630e3f442%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELook%20into%20a%20Roth%20conversion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20significant%20chunk%20of%20money%20in%20a%20pre-tax%20retirement%20account%2C%20Weeks%20suggests%20taking%20advantage%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbackdoor-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20conversion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20moving%20money%20from%20a%20traditional%20retirement%20account%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20pay%20taxes%20on%20the%20money%20you%20convert%20now%2C%20but%20all%20future%20growth%20will%20be%20completely%20tax-free.%20This%20is%20a%20smart%20move%20if%20you%20anticipate%20having%20a%20higher%20tax%20rate%20in%20the%20future%2C%20either%20due%20to%20personal%20income%20growth%20or%20legislative%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20perk%20of%20a%20Roth%20conversion%20is%20that%20once%20money%20in%20a%20qualified%20account%20gets%20converted%2C%20it's%20no%20longer%20subject%20to%20a%20required%20minimum%20distribution%2C%20which%20are%20the%20mandatory%20withdrawals%20from%20retirement%20accounts%20that%20begin%20at%20age%2073%2C%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeeks%20also%20recommends%20clients%20take%20advantage%20of%20a%20Roth%20conversion%20ladder%2C%20which%20involves%20converting%20small%20amounts%20from%20your%20traditional%20IRA%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20course%20of%20many%20years.%20By%20repeating%20this%20process%20annually%2C%20you%20can%20avoid%20jumping%20into%20a%20higher%20tax%20bracket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20looks%20like%20a%20bill%20is%20not%20forthcoming%20and%20tax%20rates%20are%20going%20to%20be%20lower%20this%20year%20than%20in%20the%20future%2C%20that%20would%20justify%20making%20a%20larger%20Roth%20conversion%20this%20year%20than%20you%20might%20have%20otherwise%20intended%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227de94af2-54d4-4259-bec8-f12e7455f87d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsider%20itemizing%20bigger%20expenses%20in%20the%20future%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20file%20your%20taxes%2C%20you%20have%20two%20options%20for%20reducing%20your%20taxable%20income%3A%20the%20standard%20deduction%20or%20itemized%20deductions.%20If%20you%20choose%20the%20standard%20deduction%2C%20you%20can%20deduct%20a%20fixed%20amount%20from%20your%20taxable%20income%2C%20with%20no%20need%20to%20document%20individual%20expenses.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20taxpayers%20might%20choose%20to%20list%20out%20specific%20expenses%20through%20itemized%20deductions%20if%20their%20expenses%20exceed%20the%20